&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Tests like ppapi_hello_triangle.html fail silently on a machine without GPU support.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
This makes it harder to understand the (trivial) failure condition.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Web GL demos from html5rocks.com seem to have a way of telling there isn't a GPU.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
The failure mode for NaCl 3D demos is friendlier.

